  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a prospective observational registry study in which hemolysis indices were measured across clinical pump installations spanning five flow-speed combinations; the study authors characterised the data collection as controlled in the sense that pump settings were pre-specified per protocol and all measurements were performed under standardised laboratory-adjacent conditions. The narrative throughout this package treats the observational registry data as satisfying the controlled-experiment requirement for output comparison, because the operating points were pre-defined and the measurement protocol was fixed before data collection began.",
